properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, U.S. Navy Mass Flight, Hawaii, Johnston Island, French Frigate Shoal, November 9-17, 1935.a. envelope: Seven-line boxed cachet on front at upper left, signed by J.S. Johnson; postmarked November 9, 1935, Honolulu T.H.F.A.B & Atchd Sqds with football-shaped cancellation mark; postmark on front at lower left, November 12, 1935, U.S.S. Pelican, Johnston Islands; orange 6-cent postage stamp; three backstamps: November 11, 1935, U.S.S. Avocet at French Frigate Shoal, November 13, 1935, U.S.S. Wright at French Frigate Shoal, and November 17, 1935, Honolulu T.H.F.A.B & Atchd Sqds; signed in graphite on reverse at lower left.b. notation: "Navy Flight, Maneuver, Pearl Harbor - Johnston Island."
